.TH hsh 1 "27 November 2019" "1.0" "Holberton SHell Maunal"

.SH NAME
hsh \- Holberton Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B echo "command" | ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION

hsh is a simple shell that works on linux systems, that executes commands from the standard input.

.SH INVOCATION

\&$ ./hsh
\&#cisfun$

Will get into interactive mode.

Or it can be use redirecting the standart output

\&$ echo "/bin/ls -l" | ./hsh

.SH FEATURES
.br
.B Display a prompt and wait for the user to type a command.
.br
.B The commands lines handle arguments
.br
.B If an executable cannot be found, print an error message and display the prompt again
.br
-B Handle the “end of file” condition (Ctrl+D) and the signal (Ctrl+C)
.br
.B Print the enviroment with 'env'


.SH BUILTINS
Builtins functions.
.br
.br
.B env
.br
-Print the environment.
.br
.B exit
-Exit with a status custom status.
.br
-exits the program
.br
.B cd
.br
- Can change the current directory to another one.

.SH BUGS
No known bugs. For the current scope, but they are going to be added has they are found.

.SH BUGS REPORTS
All bug reports go to https://github.com/juanmarcoscabezas/simple_shell, or the emails in the AUTHORS file in the repository.

